result.execSummary:
The defendant Carlos Jose Santiago Gonzalez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Aggravated Battery-Intend Bodily Harm, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(4).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Clark County Case 2015CF105 is dismissed and Read In to this case

miscConds.notes: Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety; shall not possess or consume any alcohol, and not go into places that sell alcohol except incidentally such as a grocery store, convenience store or gas station or other such place where alcohol is not sold for consumption on the premises.  Defendant shall not possess or consume any medication or drug except as may be specifically prescribed by a medical professional for defendant, and then shall be taken only as prescribed.   The defendant is to submit to an Alcohol and Other Drug Assessment (AODA) and follow the recommendations, releasing the findings to the agent.  The defendant shall attend counseling as directed by the agent, and shall make all counseling records available to the Department of Corrections.
Defendant is granted to apply for expunction after all conditions of probation have been met.

Defendant is ordered to pay the DNA surcharge, and to make arrangements to provide a DNA sample, within 48 hours, for testing through the Clark County Sheriff Department or if on probation, to the Department of Corrections as is required in all criminal convictions.

The defendant shall have no contact with Bernardo Mireles Garcia of any kind, whether direct or indirect, including in person, in writing, by phone, by e-mail or other electronic means, through a third party or in any other way.

timeConds.notes: Defendant is granted huber priveleges for work purposes or child care purposes.  Defendant is granted 3 days credit.  Defendant is to report by 9/11/16 by 5:00 pm

supervisions.notes: Defendant was granted 270 days credit for time served.
